{"source_hash": "800ee04485474f17", "candidate": {"id": "cand-011", "name": "Vivienne Chen", "raw_cv": "VIVIENNE CHEN\nvivienne.chen@email.com | Remote (London, UK)\n\nSENIOR PRODUCT MANAGER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nProduct manager with 6 years of experience in B2B SaaS, specialising in collaboration tools and developer tooling. Strong track record of shipping product from zero to one. Experienced in direct customer engagement and discovery.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Product Manager \u2014 Linear (Remote) (2022\u2013present)\n- PM for the integrations and automations product area\n- Shipped GitHub, GitLab, and Jira deep integrations adopted by 60% of the customer base\n- Led cross-functional discovery with 30+ enterprise customers to define the 2024 roadmap\n- Partnered with DevRel and Sales to create a self-serve integration framework\n\nProduct Manager \u2014 Coda (Remote) (2020\u20132022)\n- PM for the Packs (integrations) ecosystem; grew developer community from 200 to 800 active builders\n- Defined and shipped the Pack Gallery product feature\n\nAssociate PM \u2014 Dropbox, London (2018\u20132020)\n- Supported delivery of Paper collaboration product features\n\nSKILLS\nProduct strategy, developer experience, API products, user research, SQL, Mixpanel, Figma, roadmapping, A/B testing\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 University College London (2015\u20132018)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen", "raw_linkedin": "Product manager with six years building B2B SaaS products that developers actually love. Started in enterprise collaboration at Dropbox and moved to developer tooling. Currently at Linear building the integrations platform. I care about API design, developer experience, and making complex things feel simple. Fully remote advocate and async-first practitioner. Looking for PM or Head of PM roles at small to mid-size product-led companies \u2014 ideally < 200 people where I can have real influence. Not interested in large corporate environments.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Vivienne, tell me about your experience managing junior PMs.\n\nVivienne: I currently manage one associate PM at Linear and I've been mentoring informally in my previous roles. I'm keen to grow into a people management role \u2014 I enjoy coaching \u2014 but I don't yet have a team of three or four reports.\n\nInterviewer: This role does involve managing a small PM team \u2014 probably two to three people \u2014 so that experience matters.\n\nVivienne: Understood. I think I could step into that, but I'd want to be transparent that it would be a growth area for me.\n\nInterviewer: The remote setup works for you? We're fully async.\n\nVivienne: Absolutely. I've been fully remote since 2020 and I'm very comfortable with async-first culture.\n\nInterviewer: I want to ask about company size. We're at 120 employees and growing fast.\n\nVivienne: That's actually at the larger end of my preference. I love Linear and Coda because they're 50\u201380 people environments. At 120 and growing, the dynamics change quite a bit. I'd still be interested, but I want to flag that my track record is in smaller organisations. I might find the internal coordination at 200+ people less energising.\n\nInterviewer: That's good to know. Salary?\n\nVivienne: I'm on \u00a385,000. I'd be looking for \u00a388\u201392,000.", "years_experience": 6.0, "skills": ["Product strategy", "Developer experience", "API products", "User research", "SQL", "Mixpanel", "Figma", "Roadmapping", "A/B testing", "Cross-functional leadership", "Enterprise customer engagement", "Async-first practices"], "industries": ["B2B SaaS", "Collaboration tools", "Developer tooling", "Enterprise software"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "e0e5d9a8", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote working; has been fully remote since 2020 and is non-negotiable", "canonical_key": "remote_ok", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "cc72a728", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation \u00a388,000 (stated in interview: 'looking for \u00a388\u201392,000')", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96}, {"id": "c9ea3a57", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Maximum salary expectation \u00a392,000 (stated in interview: 'looking for \u00a388\u201392,000')", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 92000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96}, {"id": "b0a4b0f7", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "company_size", "description": "Preference for small to mid-size companies under 200 people; noted that 120+ employees is at the larger end of preference and internal coordination at 200+ may be less energising", "canonical_key": null, "value": "<200 people", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9}, {"id": "46d452aa", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_culture", "description": "Strongly prefers async-first culture and product-led companies; has been async-first practitioner since 2020", "canonical_key": null, "value": "async-first, product-led", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88}, {"id": "fb31aa20", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Looking for PM or Head of PM roles; open to people management growth but acknowledges limited formal team management experience (currently managing one associate PM)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "PM or Head of PM", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85}, {"id": "b3dc9dc1", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "environment", "description": "Not interested in large corporate environments; prefers smaller, more influential positions", "canonical_key": null, "value": "not large corporate", "operator": "excludes", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.87}]}, "embedding": [-0.01296048704534769, -0.00607710238546133, 0.08225411921739578, 0.0034183701500296593, -0.005564013961702585, 0.011861011385917664, 0.016285568475723267, 0.03651592507958412, -0.02137647569179535, 0.0041613494977355, 0.007109943311661482, -0.04030078649520874, 0.013133738189935684, -0.028786275535821915, 0.05517369508743286, 0.05655970051884651, -0.0471775084733963, -0.00946881901472807, -0.022455960512161255, -0.026347437873482704, 0.02626747637987137, 0.017285091802477837, -0.021629687398672104, 0.02958589419722557, 0.032064713537693024, -0.02536124177277088, -0.03931459039449692, 0.0405406728386879, -0.02214943990111351, -0.003924795426428318, 0.02325557917356491, -0.025454530492424965, -0.022842442616820335, 0.03619607537984848, -0.02260255627334118, 0.007389809936285019, -0.016445493325591087, 0.030332205817103386, 0.02947927825152874, -0.0043579223565757275, 0.005284147337079048, -0.0007583884289488196, 0.03923462703824043, 0.028999507427215576, 0.0383017398416996, -0.0036949049681425095, -0.002493811072781682, 0.01981721818447113, -0.009861964732408524, 0.020123738795518875, -0.023175617679953575, -0.058425478637218475, 0.008389333263039589, 0.07116606831550598, 0.0255344919860363, 0.0183112695813179, 0.019057581201195717, 0.016085663810372353, -0.0007937882328405976, 0.023775331676006317, 0.06679482012987137, -0.06343641877174377, 0.030332205817103386, 0.015259391628205776, -0.03523653373122215, -0.0046944282948970795, -0.04368583858013153, 0.05253495275974274, -0.003848165273666382, 0.005084242671728134, 0.02681388333439827, 0.026840535923838615, 0.012820553965866566, 0.012460725381970406, 0.03147832676768303, -0.003734885947778821, 0.019577331840991974, -0.040114209055900574, -0.02309565618634224, -0.05317464843392372, -0.07239215075969696, -0